In 2013, 187 settlements out of 288 receive subsidies from the regional budget.
The share of subsidies in the budget revenues of 122 rural settlements exceeds 50%, and 83 - one hundred percent subsidized.
Within the framework of budget provision, about 25 billion rubles are allocated from the regional budget," Oleynikov said.
The vice-governor also noted that only three urban settlements - Mytishchi, Odintsovo and Pushkino - have more than 1 billion rubles in 2013.
The income of rural settlements in many areas is less than 3 million rubles, "this is not enough at all."
