Tripody denies being influenced by Obeid
Former New South Wales Labour Minister Joe Tripody will be the subject of an investigation by the state's anti-corruption watchdog.
Former New South Wales Minister Joe Tripody denies changes to the lease of seaside properties at the request of his political mentor Eddie Obeid, who secretly owned shares in three properties on state land.
The Independent Commission Against Corruption (ICAC) on Friday expanded its investigation into whether Mr. Obeid lobbied several state ministers to extend leases to The Circular Key, where the Obeid family owns two restaurants and cafes, without going through a tender after they expired in August 2005.
It is now investigating allegations that Mr Tripody was aware of Mr Obeid's secret involvement in the properties, following testimony given by Mr Tripodi's former deputy chief of staff, Mr. Lynn Ashpole, on Thursday.
During several years of discussions that began in 2005, the government insisted that the lease be put up for open competition.
Tenants were opposed to this and also wanted longer lease terms.
In 2009, the lease agreements for The Circular Key, which brought the Obaid family about $ 2.5 million a year, were extended without being put up for public competition.
Mr. Tripodi, who was Minister of Infrastructure and Transport from February 2006 to November 2009, initially advocated for open competitions.
But he denied that the changes had been made at the request of Mr Obaid, who Mr Tripody had acknowledged had urged changes to the government's lease policy.
A transcript of telephone conversations provided by ICAC included conversations in August and September 2007 between Mr. Obaid, Mr. Tripody and Steve Dunn, a senior official who joined the Ministry of Ports after working under Mr. Obeid in the Fisheries Division.
"Was the issue discussed during these telephone conversations a question of the development of commercial lease policies?" asked Assistant Commissioner Anthony Wiley to Mr. Tripodi.
"No," Mr. Tripodi replied. —
I can't remember what was discussed, but it definitely wasn't.
Definitely not between me and Mr. Obeid.
