Eser proposes to equate insulting patriotic feelings with extremism
For the legislative protection of the patriotic feelings of citizens from provocations and insults directed against Russia, "Fair Russia" proposes to equate the insult of patriotic feelings with extremist activity and punish it with five years in prison.
According to the newspaper "Izvestia", such amendments to the legislation, prepared by the Deputy Chairman of the Duma Committee on Energy Oleg Mikheev, have already been sent for an opinion to the Supreme Court and the government.
Under the patriotic feelings of citizens, the author of the amendments proposes to understand the emotional connection of a person with the country of which he is a citizen, characterized by love for this country, a responsible attitude to its fate, respect for its history and culture.
As Mikheev points out, in domestic legislation there are sanctions for desecration of formal signs of state power - the flag and the coat of arms.
At the same time, according to the parliamentarian, the protection of Russians, whose feelings can be hurt by insulting state symbols, and other manifestations of disrespect for our country, is not sufficiently worked out in Russian legislation.
As an example, he cites the discussions that unfold annually on the eve of Victory Day, when some media personalities allow themselves to question the heroic feat of the people of the USSR in the fight against the Nazis.
On the eve of the main national holiday - Victory Day on May 9 - a real bacchanalia unfolds annually.
