Pensions to be increased in Belarus since November
Pensions have been increasing in Belarus since November of this year, BelTA learned from the main pension department of the Ministry of Labor and Social Protection.
From November 1 of this year, the average salary of employees in the republic, applied during the previous recalculation of pensions, will be adjusted with an increase in its value by 5.4% and the corresponding recalculation of labor pensions will be carried out in accordance with the decree of October 21, 2013 No. 478 "On Increasing Pensions".
As a result of the recalculation from November, labor pensions by age will increase, according to estimates, by an average of 5.3%.
The average old-age pension will be Br2 million 295 thousand.
The increase in pensions will affect 2.4 million residents of the republic.
The expenditures of the Social Protection Fund of the Ministry of Labor and Social Protection of Belarus on the payment of pensions in increased amounts from November this year will increase by Br274.3 billion per month.
Simultaneously with the recalculation of labor pensions in November of this year, minimum and social pensions, allowances, increases and additional payments to pensions will be recalculated in connection with the increase in the subsistence minimum budget on average per capita.
The BPM for the period from November 1, 2013 to January 31, 2014 was approved by the government in the amount of Br1 million 47 thousand 530 - 2.1% higher than the one in force in the period from August 1 to October 31.
Accordingly, the size of minimum labor pensions, social pensions and allowances, increases and supplements to pensions will be increased by 2.1% from November 1.
In Belarus, more than Br53 trillion has been allocated for the payment of pensions taking into account the increases in 2013.
The NSA blames an "internal error" rather than hackers for shutting down the site
Shrouded in secrecy, the National Security Agency said Friday night that shutting down their site for several hours caused a technical glitch, not hackers as claimed on the network.
